claim.claim-text:
23. A surgical fastener applying apparatus, comprising:
an anvil half-section defining a tissue contacting surface, the anvil half-section including a distal end and a proximal end that defines a longitudinal axis;
a cartridge receiving half-section including a distal end, wherein the cartridge receiving half-section is operatively couplable with the anvil half-section such that the distal end of the anvil half-section is in juxtaposed relation to the distal end of the cartridge receiving half-section, and wherein a tissue gap is defined between the distal end of the anvil half-section and the distal end of the cartridge receiving half-section when the anvil half-section and the cartridge receiving half-section are coupled together;
a deflection control system operatively associated with the anvil half-section, wherein the deflection control system reinforces the distal end of the anvil half-section when a force is applied to the distal end of the anvil half-section in a direction transverse to the longitudinal axis and normal to a plane defined by the tissue contacting surface of the anvil half-section, wherein a proximal end of the deflection control system extends proximally beyond a pivot point for the anvil half-section and the cartridge receiving half-section, the deflection control system having at least two-stages including a first stage and a second stage, wherein the deflection control system reduces a rate of deflection of the distal end of the anvil half-section in the second stage of deflection, wherein the proximal end of the deflection control system is fixedly secured to the proximal end of the anvil half-section and a distal end of the deflection control system is longitudinally slidingly coupled to the anvil half-section, and wherein the deflection control system includes a plurality of reinforcing plates each adjacent one another, at least in the distal end of the anvil half-section, the plurality of reinforcing plates being disposed adjacent a base wall of the anvil half-section; and
a pin member fixedly secured to the base wall of the anvil half-section, wherein a distal end of each of the plurality of reinforcing plates is slidingly coupled to the anvil half-section by the pin member extending through a plurality of elongate longitudinally oriented slots formed in each one of the plurality of respective reinforcing plates.

29. A surgical fastener applying apparatus, comprising:
an anvil half-section defining a tissue contacting surface, wherein the anvil half-section includes a distal end and a proximal end that defines a longitudinal axis;
a cartridge receiving half-section including a distal end, wherein the cartridge receiving half-section is operatively couplable with the anvil half-section such that the distal end of the anvil half-section is in juxtaposed relation to the distal end of the cartridge receiving half-section, and wherein a tissue gap is defined between the distal end of the anvil half-section and the distal end of the cartridge receiving half-section when the anvil half-section and the cartridge receiving half-section are coupled together;
a deflection control system operatively associated with the anvil half-section, wherein the deflection control system reinforces the distal end of the anvil half-section when a force is applied to the distal end of the anvil half-section in a direction transverse to the longitudinal axis and normal to a plane defined by the tissue contacting surface of the anvil half-section, wherein a proximal end of the deflection control system extends proximally beyond a pivot point for the anvil half-section and the cartridge receiving half-section, the deflection control system having at least two-stages including a first stage and a second stage, wherein the deflection control system reduces a rate of deflection of the distal end of the anvil half-section in the second stage of deflection, wherein a proximal end of the deflection control system is fixedly secured to a proximal end of the anvil half-section and a distal end of the deflection control system is longitudinally slidingly coupled to the anvil half-section, and wherein the deflection control system includes a plurality of reinforcing plates each adjacent one another, at least in the distal end of the anvil half-section; and
a pair of juxtaposed shoulders each extending from an inner surface of the side walls of the anvil half-section in a distal end thereof, wherein each of the plurality of reinforcing plates includes an elongate recess formed along each lateral side thereof and in operative engagement with a respective one of the pair of shoulders.
